<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-142-090  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 142 090.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Software  March 1989 v6 n2 p84(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>In Japan, open is in and successful. (Japanese softwareengineering standards projects)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Tice, George.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Several software engineering standards projects are underway inJapan in an attempt to improve software productivity and quality.andO;The Sigma project hopes to develop a network-basedhardware-independent software development environment to improvethe quality and reliability of software, enhance softwarereusability, provide a common software tool set and share softwaretechnology.andP;  Sigma's success depends on software engineeringstandards for networks and operating systems, program interfacesand environments, and distribution and information exchange.andP;  TheReal-Time Operating System Nucleus (Tron) project hopes to createan integrated, open design for microcomputer design and use;standards will be needed for microprocessor buses, local areanetworks, operating systems, user interfaces, and applicationlanguages.andP;  Standards work based on the OSI model is alsodescribed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     JapanSoftware EngineeringStandardsComputer-Aided Software EngineeringOSI StandardTRON ComputersSigma Project.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>